  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version:\r\n ```\r\nVersion: 1.7.3-unstable\r\nGit Commit: e5c19b6f98b788e6b8e7b092507a44b3808c10b8\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.7.3\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n```\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Problematics\r\n\r\nAfter update of the Geth it've worked few days in normal state. But yesterday we've noticed that it overloads CPU >150-200%. Miner options disabled, sync finished (eth_syncing results in false, height of blocks +- like on etherscan). Here is all flags that we're using at the running Geth:\r\n```\r\ngeth --verbosity 1 --port 30303 --syncmode \"full\" --identity \"mercatox\" --datadir \"/home/ethereum/node/chain\" --nousb --ipcdisable --rpc --rpcport 8540 --rpcapi \"eth,personal,admin,debug,net,rpc,txpool\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've tried to rebuild Geth few times, use 1.7.2, 1.7.1, 1.7.3 versions - no effect. Any solutions? Thanks in advance!\r\n\r\n",
